    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="692"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d692">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.754/29: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bernstein</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-15T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 15, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. After numerous conferences with King and Prime Minister, I have succeeded in
                    inducing them to approve naturalization treaty as submitted by the Department
                    with modifications authorized in the Department’s telegram No. 10 of April 14th.
                    I am informed today by the Prime Minister that Council of Ministers has finally
                    approved the treaty which will be ready for signature within a few days. If the
                    Department will give me telegraphic authorization stating that full powers are
                    being sent the treaty may be signed without delay.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bernstein</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
